Artsphere Studio Application.

Overview
This Artsphere Studio Application is a dynamic web application that allows users to browse, search, and manage a collection of artworks. Built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, it features full CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) functionality powered by json-server as a mock backend API.

Key Features
🖼️ Artwork Display: View artworks in responsive grid or list layouts

🔍 Search Functionality: Filter artworks by title or artist

✏️ CRUD Operations: Add, edit, and delete artworks

📱 Responsive Design: Works on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices

🎨 Modern UI: Clean interface with smooth transitions

Technologies Used
Frontend:

HTML5

CSS3 (Flexbox, Grid)

JavaScript (ES6+)

Fetch API for HTTP requests

Backend:

json-server (mock REST API)

db.json (database file)

Getting Started
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/art-gallery-spa.git
cd art-gallery-spa
Install json-server globally:

bash
Copy
npm install -g json-server
Start the backend server (in a separate terminal):

bash
Copy
json-server --watch db.json
Open the application:

Launch index.html in your browser

Or use a local server like VS Code's Live Server extension

